                rend="underline">they fly</hi> in the air, nor after<lb/>
they have reached the ground.<lb/>
In consequence of the alternate rising<lb/>
and sinking of the lava, according as it<lb/>
is inflated, or makes its <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">discharge</hi>, the<lb/>
depth of the crater cannot be considered<lb/>
as constant. - When the lava is at<lb/>
its height, it may be about five and<lb/>
twenty or thirty feet deep, and when<lb/>
it has subsided about forty or fifty;<lb/>
|_ the greatest rising of the lava may,<lb/>
therefore be <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">estimated</hi> at about<lb/>
twenty feet. -<lb/>
