"It was on the 23 of May 1707, at day break,<lb/>
that the first appearances of the new Island were<lb/>
perceived, slight shocks of an earthquake were<lb/>
felt and a few rocks slowly and quietly rose<lb/>
from the surface of the water. - |_ These rocks<lb/>
for three or four days presented the same<lb/>
aspect and some of the boldest inhabitants<lb/>
